1
00:00:32,007 --> 00:00:33,275
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:33,275 --> 00:00:34,510
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:34,510 --> 00:00:35,744
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:36,979
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:00:46,522 --> 00:00:48,123
He killed someone?

6
00:00:55,898 --> 00:00:58,567
He was just drunk
and talking nonsense, right?

7
00:01:55,290 --> 00:02:02,264
(Episode 5
Setting the Limit)

8
00:02:53,816 --> 00:02:54,750
So he was...

9
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:56,552
a soldier.

10
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:09,598
(Gun Accident at Special Forces Guard Post
One Dead, One Critically Injured)

11
00:03:09,598 --> 00:03:11,400
"Special forces gun accident."

12
00:03:13,468 --> 00:03:14,603
(Senior Officer Dead)

13
00:03:14,603 --> 00:03:16,305
(Special Forces Gun Accident
Sergeant Yun Receives Three-year Sentence)

14
00:03:17,706 --> 00:03:18,574
"Three-year sentence."

15
00:03:19,208 --> 00:03:20,209
"Critically injured?"

16
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:24,646
"Sergeant Yun."

17
00:03:25,781 --> 00:03:26,682
Could it be...

18
00:03:27,883 --> 00:03:28,817
Yun Deok Hyun?

19
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:35,457
Weren't you...

20
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:37,826
going to feed the cats?

21
00:03:38,627 --> 00:03:39,495
I was.

22
00:03:39,495 --> 00:03:40,863
But I left my phone behind.

23
00:03:43,999 --> 00:03:45,434
I lost my phone too,

24
00:03:46,268 --> 00:03:47,302
so I was looking for it.

25
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:50,305
Sorry if I was intruding.

26
00:03:50,305 --> 00:03:51,173
Did you see it?

27
00:04:02,084 --> 00:04:02,918
Are you...

28
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:05,420
the Sergeant Yun...

29
00:04:07,756 --> 00:04:08,957
who killed someone?

30
00:04:14,029 --> 00:04:14,897
You're not, right?

31
00:04:16,999 --> 00:04:17,833
If you're not,

32
00:04:18,367 --> 00:04:19,768
then just say so.

33
00:04:19,768 --> 00:04:22,271
Don't make me misunderstand.

34
00:04:23,005 --> 00:04:23,839
It's not...

35
00:04:26,275 --> 00:04:27,109
a misunderstanding.

36
00:04:31,547 --> 00:04:33,248
I was in prison for three years...

37
00:04:35,384 --> 00:04:36,385
for killing someone.

38
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:41,857
Why...

39
00:04:44,092 --> 00:04:45,260
did you kill them?

40
00:04:47,329 --> 00:04:48,864
Because he deserved to die.

41
00:05:09,184 --> 00:05:10,152
Hey.

42
00:05:10,819 --> 00:05:11,687
Hey!

43
00:05:12,721 --> 00:05:13,889
What are you doing?

44
00:05:14,456 --> 00:05:15,858
You seemed to be feeling uncomfortable.

45
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:17,860
I...

46
00:05:19,628 --> 00:05:20,963
It's not that...

47
00:05:23,732 --> 00:05:25,834
I can tell by the look on your face.

48
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:33,475
Just throw away my diving suit.

49
00:05:35,010 --> 00:05:36,578
Deok Hyun, where are you going?

50
00:05:37,646 --> 00:05:39,481
Wait. Are you leaving for good?

51
00:05:39,748 --> 00:05:40,883
That's so sudden!

52
00:05:40,883 --> 00:05:42,484
What's going on?

53
00:05:42,484 --> 00:05:45,254
Deok Hyun. Are you really leaving?

54
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:46,688
Deok Hyun!

55
00:05:52,861 --> 00:05:53,929
And who...

56
00:05:55,164 --> 00:05:56,031
is this guy?

57
00:05:56,331 --> 00:05:57,199
Well,

58
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,635
I'm here to see her.

59
00:06:00,536 --> 00:06:01,336
You...

60
00:06:02,337 --> 00:06:03,672
were seeing someone?

61
00:06:06,575 --> 00:06:07,476
Cha Jae Yun.

62
00:06:08,544 --> 00:06:09,411
How did you...

63
00:06:09,778 --> 00:06:10,612
Isn't this a surprise?

64
00:06:11,513 --> 00:06:12,481
I'm shocked too.

65
00:06:13,982 --> 00:06:16,685
I can't believe I came all the way
to this countryside to see you.

66
00:06:19,354 --> 00:06:21,857
I guess I do love you a lot.

67
00:06:23,959 --> 00:06:25,327
What are you waiting for?
Get your stuff.

68
00:06:29,231 --> 00:06:30,999
I'll let you swim...

69
00:06:31,834 --> 00:06:32,668
again.

70
00:06:53,989 --> 00:06:56,425
(Jeong Gi Tae)

71
00:06:59,394 --> 00:07:00,362
What?

72
00:07:00,362 --> 00:07:01,563
What's going on?

73
00:07:01,563 --> 00:07:03,131
I woke up and you were gone,

74
00:07:03,131 --> 00:07:04,833
and so was that diver girl.

75
00:07:06,502 --> 00:07:07,336
Stop crying.

76
00:07:09,905 --> 00:07:11,206
Did you run away together?

77
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:13,775
I ran away, but I don't know about her.

78
00:07:14,910 --> 00:07:16,278
Maybe she heard what you said last night.

79
00:07:17,846 --> 00:07:18,680
Me?

80
00:07:19,248 --> 00:07:20,182
What did I say?

81
00:07:22,718 --> 00:07:24,319
I always talk nonsense when I'm drunk.

82
00:07:27,156 --> 00:07:28,157
It's not nonsense.

83
00:07:34,029 --> 00:07:35,764
It's true that I got him killed.

84
00:07:51,079 --> 00:07:53,448
She must've been disappointed in me.

85
00:08:02,257 --> 00:08:04,760
I was disappointed...

86
00:08:06,628 --> 00:08:07,462
in myself.

87
00:08:10,966 --> 00:08:12,301
- Jae Yun.
- Yes?

88
00:08:12,301 --> 00:08:13,168
Hello?

89
00:08:13,168 --> 00:08:15,103
- You really went to get Seo Anna?
- Yeah.

90
00:08:15,938 --> 00:08:17,039
Why would you go and bring her back?

91
00:08:17,039 --> 00:08:19,808
You promised to break up with her
and stay with me.

92
00:08:21,743 --> 00:08:24,746
A rematch between
former youth team rivals.

93
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,415
Doesn't that sound awesome?

94
00:08:27,616 --> 00:08:29,985
And what if I end up losing?

95
00:08:29,985 --> 00:08:31,854
That's impossible.

96
00:08:35,224 --> 00:08:36,892
I know Seo Anna's skills.

97
00:08:36,892 --> 00:08:38,160
Her level is right below yours.

98
00:08:40,829 --> 00:08:43,098
Whatever. I'll leave it up to you, then.

99
00:08:45,667 --> 00:08:47,803
Jeez. She's being so annoying.

100
00:08:59,882 --> 00:09:01,350
We'll start over,

101
00:09:02,017 --> 00:09:02,851
Anna.

102
00:09:07,523 --> 00:09:08,590
I know it's silly.

103
00:09:09,791 --> 00:09:11,960
Even though I knew
what kind of person Jae Yun was,

104
00:09:14,463 --> 00:09:16,498
I came back to Seoul...

105
00:09:17,232 --> 00:09:18,667
just because he said
he'd let me swim again.

106
00:09:37,986 --> 00:09:39,888
It was as if my days in Parang-ri...

107
00:09:40,289 --> 00:09:41,890
didn't mean anything at all.

108
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,862
I think I passed three minutes.

109
00:10:20,429 --> 00:10:21,663
I did pretty well, right?

110
00:10:27,836 --> 00:10:30,005
Holding your breath for a long time
isn't what's important.

111
00:10:32,307 --> 00:10:34,743
Then why am I doing this?

112
00:10:35,944 --> 00:10:38,780
It's to know your limit.

113
00:10:40,315 --> 00:10:42,618
Lasting longer underwater
isn't always a good thing.

114
00:10:43,986 --> 00:10:45,187
You need to know your limit...

115
00:10:47,189 --> 00:10:48,891
so you know when to let go
and make it back up alive.

116
00:10:54,496 --> 00:10:55,564
Yun Deok Hyun...

117
00:10:56,798 --> 00:10:58,300
It was as though his words...

118
00:10:59,768 --> 00:11:00,669
also...

119
00:11:02,538 --> 00:11:03,605
didn't mean anything.

120
00:11:29,331 --> 00:11:30,299
(Seafood Noodles)

121
00:11:36,471 --> 00:11:39,408
These aren't seafood noodles.
They just smell like seafood.

122
00:11:49,618 --> 00:11:51,687
(Best by Sep 16, 2024)

123
00:11:51,687 --> 00:11:52,454
The limit...

124
00:11:54,356 --> 00:11:56,959
Who decides that?

125
00:12:54,783 --> 00:12:56,451
Are we seriously getting this
for Nam Seok U too?

126
00:12:56,451 --> 00:12:57,252
(Seven years ago)

127
00:12:57,252 --> 00:12:59,054
It's not because of him.
It's only because of Jae Hui.

128
00:12:59,054 --> 00:13:00,856
It's as if he's our senior.

129
00:13:03,492 --> 00:13:05,093
Darn it.

130
00:13:06,461 --> 00:13:07,729
Rock, paper, scissors.

131
00:13:10,732 --> 00:13:12,000
Go and prepare it again.

132
00:13:17,039 --> 00:13:18,073
Hurry.

133
00:13:18,073 --> 00:13:19,041
Shut up!

134
00:13:25,747 --> 00:13:27,783
You idiot. I'm holding a gun.

135
00:13:27,783 --> 00:13:28,550
Understand?

136
00:13:29,084 --> 00:13:30,018
Look.

137
00:13:30,452 --> 00:13:31,687
Please, stop.

138
00:13:31,687 --> 00:13:33,422
You must be terrified.

139
00:13:34,490 --> 00:13:35,524
Stop this, sir.

140
00:13:35,757 --> 00:13:37,125
"Stop this, sir."

141
00:13:39,528 --> 00:13:40,863
This is dangerous.

142
00:13:41,497 --> 00:13:43,131
You're right. It's dangerous.

143
00:13:43,599 --> 00:13:46,268
You could get a bullet through your head
if you're not careful.

144
00:13:47,202 --> 00:13:49,938
So just listen to me, you fucker!

145
00:13:54,443 --> 00:13:56,545
I told you to stop bullying Jae Hui.

146
00:13:56,812 --> 00:13:57,579
Didn't I?

147
00:13:59,181 --> 00:14:01,717
Why are you so bent on bullying him?

148
00:14:02,618 --> 00:14:03,452
Why?

149
00:14:05,354 --> 00:14:06,221
"Why?"

150
00:14:06,788 --> 00:14:08,524
There's no reason.

151
00:14:09,158 --> 00:14:10,092
It's just fun.

152
00:14:12,961 --> 00:14:14,229
You bastard.

153
00:14:15,430 --> 00:14:16,298
Die!

154
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:18,133
Die!

155
00:14:20,569 --> 00:14:21,403
You son of a bitch.

156
00:14:54,469 --> 00:14:56,138
Jae Hui. No.

157
00:14:56,705 --> 00:14:57,539
Jae Hui, no...

158
00:14:58,006 --> 00:14:58,841
Jae Hui.

159
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:01,944
Jae Hui...

160
00:15:01,944 --> 00:15:02,778
No.

161
00:15:03,178 --> 00:15:05,280
Jae Hui, no...

162
00:15:05,948 --> 00:15:07,683
What are you doing? Get a medic!

163
00:15:09,384 --> 00:15:10,219
Jae Hui...

164
00:15:18,861 --> 00:15:19,695
Gi Tae!

165
00:15:20,596 --> 00:15:21,663
Jeong Gi Tae!

166
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,235
What?

167
00:15:28,337 --> 00:15:29,771
- Jae Hui.
- Jae Hui!

168
00:16:30,866 --> 00:16:31,567
(Baek Su Jeong)

169
00:16:31,567 --> 00:16:32,701
Bitch.

170
00:16:33,335 --> 00:16:36,171
You haven't changed
one bit in the last ten years.

171
00:16:36,839 --> 00:16:37,739
You traitor.

172
00:16:44,146 --> 00:16:45,214
Perhaps...

173
00:16:47,049 --> 00:16:48,517
we might be struggling to survive...

174
00:16:49,084 --> 00:16:50,886
because we don't know our limits.

175
00:17:17,579 --> 00:17:19,781
We don't even know
that we've run out of breath.

176
00:17:30,592 --> 00:17:32,594
You said you were running away,
but you're here.

177
00:17:35,230 --> 00:17:36,165
Hey.

178
00:17:36,165 --> 00:17:37,032
Get up.

179
00:17:38,667 --> 00:17:39,535
Let's eat.

180
00:17:58,420 --> 00:17:59,788
What changed your mind?

181
00:18:00,088 --> 00:18:01,557
You acted like you'd never come.

182
00:18:02,457 --> 00:18:03,826
That's why I came.
So I'll never come back.

183
00:18:05,594 --> 00:18:08,497
Why do you always have to talk like that?

184
00:18:10,532 --> 00:18:12,334
Remember how you asked me
back on the island...

185
00:18:12,334 --> 00:18:14,303
why I was so obsessed with you?

186
00:18:14,970 --> 00:18:15,838
Did I?

187
00:18:18,307 --> 00:18:19,274
Well...

188
00:18:21,343 --> 00:18:22,978
I still can't forget...

189
00:18:24,947 --> 00:18:26,148
the stuff that Jae Hui said.

190
00:18:33,021 --> 00:18:35,324
Slow down. No one's stealing your food.

191
00:18:35,991 --> 00:18:37,559
It's just so tasty.

192
00:18:39,761 --> 00:18:42,364
He really isn't the Special Forces type.

193
00:18:43,131 --> 00:18:43,999
Don't you think?

194
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:45,467
There's no such thing.

195
00:18:46,001 --> 00:18:48,704
Anyone can adjust after a while.

196
00:18:54,276 --> 00:18:55,277
I...

197
00:18:55,277 --> 00:18:56,512
I actually...

198
00:18:58,413 --> 00:19:00,616
joined the Special Forces
because I wanted to change.

199
00:19:05,454 --> 00:19:07,623
I didn't want to live like this
any longer.

200
00:19:09,591 --> 00:19:10,792
There's nothing wrong with you.

201
00:19:11,593 --> 00:19:13,395
The guys who bullied you are at fault.

202
00:19:14,530 --> 00:19:15,564
Even so...

203
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:19,902
nothing will change
if I don't do anything.

204
00:19:25,107 --> 00:19:26,074
I should at least...

205
00:19:27,376 --> 00:19:28,544
make an effort.

206
00:19:39,955 --> 00:19:42,257
I wanted to bring you back out
into the world,

207
00:19:45,527 --> 00:19:47,196
but doing nothing
wouldn't change anything.

208
00:19:49,398 --> 00:19:50,365
So...

209
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,936
that's why I've been trying
all sorts of things to convince you.

210
00:20:01,577 --> 00:20:02,911
I'm sorry about this.

211
00:20:03,178 --> 00:20:05,314
I don't have a bank account.

212
00:20:06,181 --> 00:20:07,216
That's a lot.

213
00:20:07,916 --> 00:20:09,318
You're paying for several months
in advance this time?

214
00:20:10,319 --> 00:20:11,720
This is my final payment.

215
00:20:12,554 --> 00:20:13,822
You've been paying for two years,

216
00:20:13,822 --> 00:20:15,791
but it was your first visit, wasn't it?

217
00:20:16,458 --> 00:20:17,826
There are lots of people like you.

218
00:20:18,327 --> 00:20:21,029
It's not easy to see
your loved ones in pain.

219
00:20:23,298 --> 00:20:25,400
Yeah, well... I guess.

220
00:20:26,969 --> 00:20:27,936
How did it go?

221
00:20:32,341 --> 00:20:34,076
He asked why you didn't
come sooner, right?

222
00:20:40,349 --> 00:20:41,450
Come back next time.

223
00:20:41,984 --> 00:20:43,886
We only accept
one month's payment at a time.

224
00:20:52,194 --> 00:20:53,362
I'm sorry.

225
00:20:53,362 --> 00:20:54,930
Please just accept it.

226
00:21:26,094 --> 00:21:27,429
I admire your courage.

227
00:21:28,497 --> 00:21:31,433
I didn't work up the courage.
I'm here to check my limit.

228
00:21:31,834 --> 00:21:32,901
What are you on about?

229
00:21:32,901 --> 00:21:33,902
Come on.

230
00:21:34,570 --> 00:21:35,704
Stop chatting.

231
00:21:36,738 --> 00:21:37,906
Let's start with a warm-up.

232
00:21:38,407 --> 00:21:39,241
Get ready...

233
00:21:53,889 --> 00:21:54,723
Hey.

234
00:21:55,524 --> 00:21:57,626
I heard you brought her back here.

235
00:21:57,626 --> 00:21:58,594
Are you kidding me?

236
00:21:58,961 --> 00:21:59,795
What?

237
00:22:00,729 --> 00:22:02,297
You liked her too, didn't you?

238
00:22:02,798 --> 00:22:03,665
Well...

239
00:22:03,966 --> 00:22:05,601
I like looking at her,

240
00:22:06,168 --> 00:22:08,370
but she has a nasty temper.

241
00:22:08,370 --> 00:22:10,439
Then just watch her quietly.

242
00:22:10,973 --> 00:22:12,241
If she's nice to look at, then it's fine.

243
00:22:13,075 --> 00:22:13,909
Shall I?

244
00:22:18,213 --> 00:22:19,481
She does give me butterflies.

245
00:22:20,949 --> 00:22:21,817
So,

246
00:22:22,251 --> 00:22:24,653
you're going to make her an athlete again?

247
00:22:26,054 --> 00:22:26,989
Of course not.

248
00:22:28,056 --> 00:22:30,459
She can't be an athlete with those skills.

249
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:32,594
Ye Kyung...

250
00:22:32,995 --> 00:22:34,730
wasn't practicing hard these days,

251
00:22:35,397 --> 00:22:36,565
so I wanted to motivate her and stuff.

252
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:38,834
"And stuff?"

253
00:22:39,434 --> 00:22:40,269
I wanted...

254
00:22:41,236 --> 00:22:42,838
to sleep with Anna too.

255
00:22:46,008 --> 00:22:48,277
You're insane.

256
00:22:49,111 --> 00:22:50,546
Ye Kyung's sexy...

257
00:22:50,979 --> 00:22:52,347
and Anna's cute.

258
00:22:53,215 --> 00:22:54,683
They're both my style.

259
00:23:00,155 --> 00:23:03,058
To be honest, I already knew...

260
00:23:04,059 --> 00:23:05,460
that this was my limit.

261
00:23:17,773 --> 00:23:18,640
I just...

262
00:23:19,474 --> 00:23:21,009
couldn't let go until now.

263
00:23:55,644 --> 00:23:56,945
It wasn't going to take long.

264
00:23:59,581 --> 00:24:00,649
You'll get yourself killed like that.

265
00:24:01,583 --> 00:24:02,851
You need to let go and come back up.

266
00:24:03,986 --> 00:24:04,987
That's how you survive.

267
00:24:08,390 --> 00:24:09,658
Was Yun Deok Hyun right?

268
00:24:10,826 --> 00:24:13,595
Would I survive if I let go?

269
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:19,768
Can I really survive...

270
00:24:20,903 --> 00:24:21,870
even if I...

271
00:24:23,238 --> 00:24:24,306
give up swimming?

272
00:24:26,475 --> 00:24:28,977
You're not satisfied
with Han Ye Kyung alone?

273
00:24:30,679 --> 00:24:32,381
Can you really handle both of them?

274
00:24:32,381 --> 00:24:33,315
Hey, Seo Anna!

275
00:24:33,882 --> 00:24:35,250
Why are you stopping? Keep going!

276
00:24:38,954 --> 00:24:40,422
Where is she going?

277
00:24:40,856 --> 00:24:41,657
What?

278
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:46,161
What?

279
00:24:49,164 --> 00:24:50,065
Are you hurting?

280
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,034
Is it your shoulder?

281
00:24:56,672 --> 00:24:57,506
Are you crazy?

282
00:24:57,506 --> 00:24:58,774
Yeah, I am.

283
00:24:59,741 --> 00:25:01,777
You can't swim if you treat me like this.

284
00:25:02,177 --> 00:25:03,078
I won't, you jerk.

285
00:25:10,919 --> 00:25:11,854
Seo Anna.

286
00:25:13,155 --> 00:25:14,089
Have you lost your mind?

287
00:25:14,523 --> 00:25:15,390
Asshole.

288
00:25:17,693 --> 00:25:19,561
I didn't say anything.

289
00:25:20,696 --> 00:25:21,563
You jerk.

290
00:25:24,533 --> 00:25:27,002
I wasn't planning
on talking it out either.

291
00:25:29,104 --> 00:25:30,072
Han Ye Kyung.

292
00:25:31,406 --> 00:25:32,908
If you keep rolling like that,

293
00:25:34,109 --> 00:25:35,110
you'll end up like me.

294
00:25:37,746 --> 00:25:38,881
Don't trust Coach Cha...

295
00:25:42,718 --> 00:25:43,719
too much.

296
00:25:57,166 --> 00:25:59,268
(Award)

297
00:26:01,136 --> 00:26:02,104
I'm sorry.

298
00:26:02,738 --> 00:26:04,773
I'll find the next tenant myself,

299
00:26:04,773 --> 00:26:06,375
- so just for a month...
- All right.

300
00:26:06,809 --> 00:26:08,443
But you're so young.

301
00:26:08,443 --> 00:26:10,679
Why are you suddenly moving
to the countryside?

302
00:26:14,983 --> 00:26:15,951
I have to...

303
00:26:16,785 --> 00:26:18,520
let things go and go above water...

304
00:26:19,888 --> 00:26:21,056
to survive.

305
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:27,062
Yes, please do that for me.

306
00:26:28,063 --> 00:26:28,997
Thank you.

307
00:26:45,013 --> 00:26:45,848
Mom.

308
00:26:47,483 --> 00:26:48,817
I'm doing a good job,

309
00:26:49,918 --> 00:26:50,752
right?

310
00:26:51,854 --> 00:26:53,555
There's no need to ask.

311
00:27:00,863 --> 00:27:01,864
Gosh.

312
00:27:02,598 --> 00:27:04,833
When did you ever do what I said...

313
00:27:04,833 --> 00:27:06,335
and stop when I told you to?

314
00:27:07,269 --> 00:27:08,971
You never listened to a word I said.

315
00:27:11,473 --> 00:27:12,941
When did I do that?

316
00:27:15,043 --> 00:27:16,078
I told you,

317
00:27:17,146 --> 00:27:20,716
the color of your medal doesn't matter
the slightest bit.

318
00:27:21,817 --> 00:27:22,684
And it's the same now.

319
00:27:23,519 --> 00:27:26,021
Whether you swim or not doesn't matter.

320
00:27:28,857 --> 00:27:30,659
My daughter, Seo Anna.

321
00:27:31,226 --> 00:27:34,263
Just do what you want, eat healthy,

322
00:27:34,530 --> 00:27:35,531
and live a comfortable life.

323
00:27:35,998 --> 00:27:36,932
That's all I want for you.

324
00:27:41,970 --> 00:27:45,040
I'll always be rooting for you.

325
00:27:48,544 --> 00:27:49,578
Seo Anna,

326
00:27:49,578 --> 00:27:50,512
stay strong!

327
00:28:17,072 --> 00:28:18,907
Do it properly.

328
00:28:18,907 --> 00:28:20,843
Come on, you little brat!

329
00:28:23,679 --> 00:28:24,880
I don't want to do this.

330
00:28:26,715 --> 00:28:29,818
I should've been the one
to go to Seoul, not Anna.

331
00:28:33,121 --> 00:28:34,323
It's not too late, you know.

332
00:28:41,129 --> 00:28:43,265
What? You're back already?

333
00:28:43,565 --> 00:28:45,234
Yeah, I am.

334
00:28:54,409 --> 00:28:55,377
How have you been?

335
00:29:07,189 --> 00:29:08,090
In the end...

336
00:29:09,791 --> 00:29:10,959
I came back to Parang-ri.

337
00:29:14,163 --> 00:29:15,063
But...

338
00:29:15,764 --> 00:29:16,865
things are different from before.

339
00:29:24,573 --> 00:29:26,408
Because the fact that I came back up...

340
00:29:33,215 --> 00:29:35,284
means I'm ready to dive back in.

341
00:29:36,985 --> 00:29:37,920
I'm so hungry.

342
00:29:42,224 --> 00:29:44,660
(Parang-ri diver Jo Mi Hyun)

343
00:30:25,767 --> 00:30:28,203
You're here.

344
00:30:30,205 --> 00:30:31,006
Were you...

345
00:30:32,508 --> 00:30:33,876
waiting for me?

346
00:30:37,613 --> 00:30:39,982
I came to tell you something
before I left.

347
00:30:47,256 --> 00:30:49,158
If it's an explanation about your past,

348
00:30:50,092 --> 00:30:50,959
there's no need.

349
00:30:52,294 --> 00:30:53,495
I didn't look up anything,

350
00:30:54,897 --> 00:30:56,031
and I'm not even curious.

351
00:30:57,466 --> 00:30:58,634
If you're really a bad guy,

352
00:31:00,202 --> 00:31:01,737
the police would've arrested you already.

353
00:31:06,975 --> 00:31:08,010
More than anything,

354
00:31:11,713 --> 00:31:13,015
it's not something...

355
00:31:14,917 --> 00:31:16,385
I should receive an apology for
or forgive.

356
00:31:27,696 --> 00:31:28,530
You should...

357
00:31:31,266 --> 00:31:32,334
swim again.

358
00:31:37,239 --> 00:31:39,107
That's what I came here to tell you.

359
00:31:42,411 --> 00:31:44,546
I was afraid I wouldn't be able to live...

360
00:31:45,547 --> 00:31:46,415
after quitting swimming.

361
00:31:51,353 --> 00:31:52,988
You know you're being silly, don't you?

362
00:31:57,092 --> 00:31:58,760
I felt it while I saw you diving.

363
00:31:58,760 --> 00:31:59,661
You...

364
00:32:00,529 --> 00:32:01,630
can swim again.

365
00:32:02,698 --> 00:32:04,700
Are you giving advice to a professional?

366
00:32:08,303 --> 00:32:09,238
Sorry.

367
00:32:10,272 --> 00:32:11,573
It wasn't my place.

368
00:32:14,076 --> 00:32:16,712
But I'm not scared anymore.

369
00:32:26,255 --> 00:32:27,723
I'm glad you seem okay.

370
00:32:29,024 --> 00:32:29,858
Well, then.

371
00:32:33,896 --> 00:32:34,863
Do you want...

372
00:32:37,699 --> 00:32:38,734
to swim together?

373
00:32:46,608 --> 00:32:47,476
This time,

374
00:32:50,012 --> 00:32:51,146
I'll teach you.

375
00:32:59,655 --> 00:33:01,623
Because now I know that there's someone...

376
00:33:04,726 --> 00:33:05,961
willing to dive into the water...

377
00:33:08,030 --> 00:33:09,097
with me.

378
00:33:33,489 --> 00:33:34,523
What?

379
00:33:34,523 --> 00:33:36,525
How did you know where I live?

380
00:33:36,992 --> 00:33:37,793
Jeez.

381
00:33:37,793 --> 00:33:41,163
I've been chasing Yun Deok Hyun around
for three years.

382
00:33:41,463 --> 00:33:44,967
Tracking down an athlete whose name
and face are known is a piece of cake.

383
00:33:47,202 --> 00:33:48,804
Why are you here, then?

384
00:33:52,441 --> 00:33:54,409
Yun Deok Hyun...

385
00:33:55,010 --> 00:33:56,912
It seems like he went back to the island.

386
00:33:59,214 --> 00:34:01,750
No way. He took his stuff and left.

387
00:34:03,485 --> 00:34:05,020
I'm sure of it.

388
00:34:06,221 --> 00:34:07,156
So...

389
00:34:07,890 --> 00:34:09,091
if you meet him again,

390
00:34:11,293 --> 00:34:12,194
can you...

391
00:34:13,729 --> 00:34:15,063
pull him out of the water?

392
00:34:20,736 --> 00:34:22,437
I saw how he was smiling...

393
00:34:24,606 --> 00:34:26,074
when he was with you.

394
00:34:30,979 --> 00:34:31,847
Hey!

395
00:34:38,687 --> 00:34:39,588
He was smiling...

396
00:34:40,689 --> 00:34:42,291
when he was with me?

397
00:34:49,198 --> 00:34:50,465
Get up.

398
00:35:26,335 --> 00:35:28,337
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
